# DEPLOYMENT EXAMPLES
# -----------------------------------------

# Railway:
# MCP_PLAYWRIGHT_URL=https://playwright-production.up.railway.app/mcp
# MCP_CLAUDE_SKILLS_URL=https://claude-skills-production.up.railway.app/mcp

# Render:
# MCP_PLAYWRIGHT_URL=https://playwright.onrender.com/mcp
# MCP_CLAUDE_SKILLS_URL=https://claude-skills.onrender.com/mcp

# Vercel (via external service):
# MCP_PLAYWRIGHT_URL=https://mcp-playwright.example.com/mcp
# MCP_CLAUDE_SKILLS_URL=https://mcp-claude.example.com/mcp

# Docker Compose:
# MCP_PLAYWRIGHT_URL=http://playwright:3100/mcp
# MCP_CLAUDE_SKILLS_URL=http://claude-skills:3101/mcp

# -----------------------------------------
# VALIDATION
# -----------------------------------------
# In production (NODE_ENV=production), the system will:
# 1. Check if URLs are still using localhost
# 2. Fail with clear error message if not configured
# 3. Log when environment variables are used
#
# Error example:
# "Production environment detected but playwright is using
#  localhost URL. Set MCP_PLAYWRIGHT_URL environment variable."

# -----------------------------------------
# TESTING
# -----------------------------------------
# Test your configuration:
# 1. Set environment variables
# 2. Run: npm run dev
